	  bugpatch.

2005-05-11 17:57  loose

	* assay, runtest.sh: %[ER: 252]%

	  * Runtest now takes a second (optional) argument that specifies
	  the maximum	number of seconds the test is allowed to run.  *
	  Assay should now be called using <max run-time> as first
	  argument!   This was the only way to implement this feature
	  properly, because assay can	(in principle) run any executable
	  taking any number of arguments.

2005-05-11 11:29  schaaf

	* variants: %[ER: 275]% Added blrts.compiler definition.  This one
	  should be used for the Blue Gene cross compilations.	The old
	  xlc.compiler variant will lated be redefined to "normal" xlc in
	  order to compile for the normal host target architecture (e.g.
	  the BG FENS).

