2005-02-01 13:36  lofar

	* scanBuildLog: %[ER:71 ]% changed comparision with None into
	  "None"

2005-01-28 11:16  loose

	* slash2spanning.pl: %[ER: 234]%

	  Undid the latest changes. For reasons beyond my comprehension
	  Doxygen would still filter *.h files when they are
	  \verbinclude-ed in e.g. a *.doc file. However, you can specify
	  FILTER_PATTERNS in the Doxygen configuration file (which is a
	  rather new variable). Specifying only *.h and *.idl as
	  FILTER_PATTERNS solves the original problem: only filter files
	  that have the specified suffixes.

2005-01-27 15:44  loose

	* slash2spanning.pl: %[ER: 234]%

	  Now only files with suffix ".h" of ".idl" are being filtered;
	  others are left untouched.

2005-01-27 09:21  loose

	* makedep.sh: %[ER: 30]%

	  * Added standard header and, more importantly, #!/bin/sh line.  *
	  Added check for existence of pkgdep program.

