	  /usr/local/include to search path; g++ doesn't like it.

2003-10-08 18:04  mueller

	* lofar_pvss.m4: %[ER: 34]%

2003-10-02 09:45  diepen

	* Makefile.common: %[PR: 31]% Had to use $(CXX) instead of $(CC) in
	  preprocessing .cc file

2003-09-15 13:45  loose

	* Makefile.common: %[ER: 24]% Add test directory to exclude list
	  for doxygen

2003-09-04 11:58  loose

	* lofar_init.m4: Added check for endianness. If system is
	  big-endian WORDS_BIGENDIAN will be defined.

2003-09-04 11:57  loose

	* variants.lofar9: Added the Intel C++ compiler (icc) to the
	  variants list.

2003-09-02 19:24  loose

	* slash2spanning.pl: In order to ensure that the line numbers in
	  the annotated source file that is generated by Doxygen will match
	  with the real source file, the following changes were made: -
	  Lines starting with "slash-slash-hash" (//#) are now replaced
	  with blank   lines, instead of being discarded.  - The
	  start-comment (/**) and end-comment (*/) tokens are not put on a
	  separates lines anymore.

2003-09-01 14:05  diepen

	* lofarconf_recur: cd ../.. only needed at beginning of each make
	  target

2003-08-29 18:54  loose

	* lofar_docxx.m4: - Doxygen now uses the input filter
	  "slash2spanning.pl" which converts   multiple C++-style comment
	  lines (// a comment) into a spanning C-style	 comment (/*...*/).
	  Comment lines starting with "slash-slash-hash"   (//# a comment)
	  are completely ignored.  - Changed default search path for
	  doxygen, dot, and doc++ to /usr/bin.

2003-08-29 17:39  loose

	* slash2spanning.pl: Lines starting with "slash-slash-hash" style
	  comments (//# a comment) are now completely ignored. The asterisk
	  "*" in the C-style comment is no longer repeated on every line;
	  they pollute \verbatim and \code sections in Doxygen.

2003-08-29 17:05  loose

	* slash2spanning.pl: Original version, by John Moren.

2003-08-29 10:59  diepen

	* lofar_external.m4: Also look in given directory for
	  headers/libraries

