	  Added MPE_Log_event statements to profile MeqTree functionality.

2003-01-15 11:38  wierenga

	* profiletool: %[BugId: 161]%

	  remove debugging output

2003-01-15 11:17  wierenga

	* lofar_mpi.m4, profiletool, variants: %[BugId: 161]%

	  First version of profiletool.

	  Fixed lofar_mpi.m4 to correctly handle optional profiling. Added
	  MPIBIN variable which can be used in Makefile.am's to find path
	  to mpirun (e.g. $(MPIBIN)/mpirun).

	  Added profile variant which is currently defines as

	  profile.var: --with-optimize='-pg -O4' --with-compiletools
	  --with-mpich --enable-mpi-profiler

2003-01-14 12:26  schaaf

	* variants:
	  %[BugId: 117]% Removed default aip++ usage for scampi

2003-01-14 10:05  wierenga

	* compiletool, lofar_qatools.m4, variants: %[BugId: 160]%

	  Add --with-compiletools option in lofar_qatools to invoke
	  LOFAR/autoconf_share/compiletool as the compiler. This script
	  logs the compile command and invokes the command.

	  The profile variant uses the --with-compiletools options.

	  The compiletool script currently only logs the compile line for
	  binaries and libraries (via the LIBTOOL variable). It does not
	  log invokations of CC or CXX (which are used to produce object
	  files).

2003-01-08 12:05  wierenga

	* lofarconf: %[BugId: 76]%

	  Now really fixed quote handling by running the configure with
	  'eval'.

2003-01-08 11:36  wierenga

	* lofarconf: %[BugId: 76]%

	  Added missing quotes around "$opts" variable when executing the
	  configure command.  The missing quotes where causing the
	  following to fail:

	  in variants file:

		  profile.var:	  --with-cxxflags='-pg -O4'
	  --with-cflags='-pg -O4'

	  Whithout the quotes -O4' would be considered as a separate
	  argument instead of as a part of the --with-cxxflags argument.

